snippet.textDisplay:
I'm seeing a lot of comments about fans attacking Dan, but very few actually attacking him. Let's keep this civil and not make this harder on anyone. Even if you don't like Dan from all this, remember Hosuh and the others are still here having to deal with the backlash for what they had no part in. But also realize that criticism is not an attack, and it's okay to state one's view as long as it's measured and not hostile.

We don't have Dan's comment on the situation yet, and I am eagerly awaiting it, but that doesn't mean we shouldn't at least be mentioning this issue because he hasn't commented yet. As far as anyone can tell, this is a real issue that needs to be discussed, and hopefully Dan will release a statement and give us a clearer picture instead of hoping it all blows over. You can't just attack Dan without hurting the others, even if you feel he should be attacked. We're here because we support the team as a whole, but at the same time, that's the reason for this outcry; we supported them as a team, and from what we've heard so far that's not how our support was distributed.
